my decision, and that I did consider moving them, but decided against it.  I also want to be clear that I agree with the decision to make it expansion only, even if I may not like it.  Sometimes a choice has to be made whether I like it or not :) We need to make money on the expansions, and we need to put in it things that players want, or we will not get money from the expansion.  With that in mind, we cannot just freely give it out then, if we want to make money from it.  Again there is that fact that we are a business.  I love tradeskills, but I definitely want to be paid for doing this job, I am not quite so magnanimous as to do this much work for free :)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Message Edited by Dev-Ngreth on &lt;span class="date_text"&gt;03-29-2006&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="time_text"&gt;10:18 AM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;Na. It is nothing about lazy nor about your decisions.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;More about the vision and thoughts that should have gone into stuff like that on the producer side of eq.  In operations there is only so much you can think of yourself, thats why the producer has to work the thoughttrains thru to the end and decide on that. Once the decision was in place- who-ever made it, it gets harder each day to go back on that one. Once you have that much code added, it is basicly too late&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;If this had been thought of at the very start, it would have been easy to design a safespot in the expansion, not accessible to the non por enabled people.  As is, it made quite a few happy so in the end it works out anyway.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Anyway, is it the intention that tradeskill trophees can not outlevel their owners? If so, there is a bug somewhere- seeing i have a master fletching trophee but 298 skill&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
